verb + infinite + adjective

When we speculate about someone or something, we can use use a verb + to be + an adjective. 
Commom verbs that can be used in this way include verbs of appearance of feeling such as appear, look, seem, be supposed, pretend, etc.

The test doesn't seem to be difficult.

It was supposed to be easy.

She's pretending to be cool.

The children appear to be happy.

She looks to be thirty years old.
